textarea_set_background
#include Style
#Background wimp 1
#Parent textarea
Header:	<textarea.h=>textarea_gadget>
#Line
#Wrap off
Syntax:	
#indent 6
{FCode}extern <_kernel_oserror> *textarea_set_background
(
  unsigned int <flags=>textarea_set_background_flags>,
  <ObjectId>     window, 
  <ComponentId>  textarea,
  void        *sprite_area,
  void        *sprite,
  int          x_off,
  int          y_off
);              

{F}
#indent
#Wrap
Purpose:	Function sets a sprite to be rendered as a background to the text (requires <TextGadgets=>textgadgets/m> 0.23). {/}x_off{/} and {/}y_off{/} are plot offsets in OS coordinates and allow the position of the sprite to be adjusted. Tiling and base alignment are controlled by the <gadget state=>textarea_flags>.
	Various extensions require TextGadgets 0.77:
	è	Sprites can be specified by name instead of pointer by setting {/}flags{/} bit 0.
	è	Any background sprite is removed if {/}sprite_area{/} == 0.
	è	Sprites from the Wimp pool (which must be referred to by name) can be used by specifying {/}sprite_area{/} == 1.
